This article is a presidential order issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. in the United States. The order establishes the National Quantum Initiative Advisory Committee, which will provide advice and recommendations on the National Quantum Initiative (NQI) Program. The committee will consist of the Director of the Office of Science and Technology Policy and up to 26 members appointed by the President, representing industry, universities, and federal laboratories. The committee will meet regularly, respond to requests for information and analysis, review the national strategy for quantum information science, and provide recommendations to the President. The heads of agencies will provide information to the committee when requested, and the committee may establish subcommittees and ad hoc groups. The National Quantum Coordination Office will provide support to the committee. The committee members will serve without compensation but may receive travel expenses. This order revokes a previous executive order on the same subject. The order is implemented in accordance with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations.